\begin_layout FrameSubtitle
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

Algebra of events
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{definition}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 denotes the sample space of a given experiment and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

 a collection of events.
 We say that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

 is a 
\emph on

\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra
\emph default
 over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 if 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

 is a
\emph on
n algebra
\emph default
 over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{n}\in\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $n=1,2,\ldots$
\end_inset

, then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bigcup_{n=1}^{\infty}E_{n}\in\mathcal{F}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{definition}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Interpretation: a 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is a family of subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 which is closed with respect to
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the difference operator 
\begin_inset Formula $\setminus$
\end_inset

 (or equivalently complementation),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the 
\emph on
countable
\emph default
 union and intersection of its elements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout EndFrame

\end_layout

\begin_layout BeginFrame
Basic definitions
\end_layout

\begin_layout FrameSubtitle
Algebra and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

Algebra generation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

 be a collection of subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 Then there are a smallest algebra 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\mathcal{E})$
\end_inset

 and a smallest 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma(\mathcal{E})$
\end_inset

 containing all the set that are in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}(S)$
\end_inset

 is a 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra on 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore it exists at least one 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra and one algebra containing 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

.
 We define 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\mathcal{E})$
\end_inset

 (or 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma(\mathcal{E})$
\end_inset

) to consist of all sets that belong to every algebra (or 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra) containing 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

.
 It is easy to verify that this system is an algebra (or 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-algebra$
\end_inset

) and indeed the smallest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout EndFrame

\end_layout

\begin_layout BeginFrame
Basic definitions
\end_layout

\begin_layout FrameSubtitle
Algebra and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

Algebra generation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Examples

\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 be the family of open intervals on the real line, i.e.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{C}:=\{(a,b)\mid a,b\in\mathbb{R}\mbox{ and }a<b\}.
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}(\mathbb{R}):=\sigma(\mathcal{C})$
\end_inset

 is called the Borel sigma algebra over 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $f:S\rightarrow\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 be a real valued function.
 The family of preimages:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\{f^{-1}(B):B\in\mathcal{B}(\mathbb{R})\}
\]

\end_inset

 is a 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra on 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, the 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-$
\end_inset

algebra generated by 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 [denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma(f)$
\end_inset

].
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout EndFrame

\end_layout

